Your Digest for Thursday, Apr 04, 2024 08:59 AM

Source

  • Internal capsule strokes are differentiated from cortical strokes by the absence of cortical deficits.

    • Cortical deficits are as seizures, aphasia, agnosia, and dysgraphia, apraxia, alexia, and amnesia, neglect syndromes etc.

  • Typical internal capsule stroke syndromes are

    1. Pure motor stroke (i.e hemiparesis)
    2. Hemiparesis with ataxia
    3. Clumsy hand - dysarthria

  • Blood supply of the internal capsule:

    • Lipohyalinosis of perforating arteries is the most common cause of lacunar strokes

LS = lenticulostriate
